      "content": "I see. But \"momentum\" is hard to sell without a hard number. If I tell them the data is \"nuanced,\" they're going to ask for a confidence percentage to justify the risk. \n\nIf I tell them we're looking at an 85% or 90% confidence level in these projections, does that actually cross the line into being a lie, or is it just a reasonable interpretation of the upward trend you mentioned? I need to know how much I can lean into this so we don't lose the funding.",
